text.section:
A nonappropriated fund instrumentality established under this section may:
Contract for goods and services;
Hire nonappropriated fund employees under terms and conditions as it may negotiate, subject only to applicable state and federal labor laws;
Establish a system of bookkeeping, accounting, and auditing procedures for the proper handling of funds derived from its operations; and
Perform any other action necessary to establish a board, corporation, or other entity for the purpose of operating the morale, welfare, and recreation facilities.
